        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Location of localhost folder in Ubuntu 12.04",
        "body": "<p>I'm running eclipse Juno, with Tomcat 7.0.29. I have some files that are saved to the root of the webapp by my webapp and I want to delete them. I'm trying to find the localhost folder in order to be able to do this. Everything I'm reading tells me it should be at /var/www, however there is not /www directory in var. Where could it be?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 14983703,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "eclipse",
            "tomcat"
        ],
        "score": 0,
        "accepted_answer_id": 14984586,
