            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1361376725,
            "creation_date": 1361376725,
            "body": "<p>Since you're using Eclipse IDE and you don't know where your Tomcat installation folder is, you can find it using the IDE by going to <em>Windows/Preferences<\/em>. It will pop a Preferences window, select the <em>Server/Runtime Environment<\/em> option in the left tree, in the right side must appear <em>Apache Tomcat v7.x<\/em>. Select it from the list and select the <em>Edit...<\/em> option, it will show you the tomcat installation directory. Let's call this folder <code>&lt;tomcat&gt;<\/code><\/p>\n\n<p>Now you know the folder installation, but maybe Eclipse is not using it to deploy the Java Web applications. To make sure of this, in your Eclipse, go to the <em>Servers<\/em> view (if it's not visible in the IDE, go to <em>Window/Show view/Servers<\/em>), it will show you your tomcat server (and others), double click on it. In the Tomcat overview window, check the <em>Server locations<\/em> panel, expand it and check where the webapp is deployed:<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>If selected option is <em>Use Tomcat installation<\/em> then the web app must be in <em><code>&lt;tomcat&gt;<\/code>webapps<\/em><\/li>\n<li>If selected option is <em>Use workspace metadata<\/em> then the web app must be in your workspace inside <em>.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.wst.server.core/tmp[number]/wtpwebapps<\/em> (thanks to <a href=\"http://www.vogella.com/blog/2009/04/08/eclipse-wtp-deployment-location-of-the-local-tomcat/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lars Vogel blog post<\/a>). This is a special folder created by Eclipse.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
            "answer_id": 14984586,
            "question_id": 14983703
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/k1TDL.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1668674,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1535575,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1535575/rootkit",
                "reputation": 2165,
                "display_name": "rootkit",
                "accept_rate": 75
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1361375243,
            "creation_date": 1361374467,
            "body": "<p>Default tomcat folder is at /var/lib/tomcat7. Your webapps are under /var/lib/tomcat7/webapps<\/p>\n\n<p>Not sure what localhost folder you are referring to. There is /etc/tomcat7/Catalina/localhost but I dont see a reason why you should be touching it. <\/p>\n\n<p>This assumes you used standard Ubuntu tools to install tomcat. <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 14983757,
            "question_id": 14983703,
            "last_edit_date": 1361375243
        }
    ],
